    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom are turning kinda yellow and pale compared to the top ones. what's probably going on with them?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That yellowing at the bottom of your tomato plants is likely a natural sign of the plant shedding old growth to conserve energy for the fruit and new leaves above. It is often called \"senescence\" or simply the plant aging, though it can sometimes indicate nutrient deficiencies or water stress if the yellowing spreads quickly to the rest of the plant. Since you mentioned the top leaves are still green, your plants are probably still healthy and just prioritizing their reproductive stage. You should check for pests like aphids or spider mites, which can also cause yellowing, and ensure you are watering the base of the stem rather than the leaves to prevent fungal issues.",
      "source": "target",
